BLOEMFONTEIN – Democratic Alliance leader in the Free State Patricia Kopane has been re-elected to the position at the party’s provincial elective congress on Saturday. READ: Bonginkosi Madikizela elected DA Western Cape acting leader Annelie Lotriet was elected provincial chairperson, with Carina Serfontein as her deputy. David van Vuuren was elected financial chairperson, the DA said in a statement on Sunday. “These are the leaders tasked with leading the party in the Free State and building sustainable structures that will further strengthen the organisation in order to achieve victory in 2019 and beyond,” Kopane said in the statement. African News Agency